{"Q0":"I suppose the brain tends to try and find pattern out of chaos, I naturally tried to find a comparative pattern between the A and the B images over time, and halfway through the experiment I realized that B seemed to be the mirror image of A--or A played backwards. In real life, attention is drawn by whatever \"excites\" our senses in the world we're perceiving, so I wouldn't expect perfect predictability in how our attention \"unfolds,\" so to speak. But, assuming a world that we are at liberty to perceive/\"read,\" our understanding tends to move left to right (at least my literate mind does). It was at that moment that I realized that the perception patterns that seemed more human were the ones displaying mostly a left-to-right trajectory. This is just a hypothesis, but it helped cement my level of confidence going forward."}
